title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 shows obfuscated classes, such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd', etc.
OB: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 displays obfuscated classes.
EB: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 should only display non-obfuscated classes.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Open the All types dialog in JDK 1.4.
2. Observe the presence of obfuscated classes.
